Reasoning: The paper focuses on two extended models of finite automata, namely finite automata over groups and homing vector automata. These models are primarily related to formal language theory (cs.FL) and group theory (cs.GR). The paper also discusses decision problems of matrix semigroups, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper presents new results about valence pushdown automata and context-free valence grammars, which are related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
